<p>Australia is the second favorite destination after Canada when it comes to Immigration. Friendly laws and a demand for skilled workers continues to drive people to the 'island country'. The excellent education system adds to the number by providing an easy pathway for students looking for a ‘better life’. For the latter, however, it becomes extremely important to understand the popular job sectors that have a steady demand for professionals so as to facilitate the choice of the right courses to opt for. Here’s a list of the top sectors that have a steady demand and would continue to increase the numbers in the years to come.</p>
<p><strong>1. Education</strong></p>
<p>Australia’s population is on the rise, reporting a more than positive incline in its trend. As such, there is a strong demand for quality education and in turn of quality educationists. This is more prevalent for primary teachers and language teachers. The industry expects to see a double-digit growth of 13.3 percent by 2019.</p>
<p>So, if teaching excites you, then you are sure to find a relevant job in Australia. The qualifications would ideally include specialists in primary teaching and training as well as specialists counselors. Accordingly, the hot courses would include Masters in Education. Also, most of the TAFE Institutes offer excellent certificate programs which can facilitate the transition into the country. </p>
<p><strong>2. Healthcare and Medical</strong></p>
<p>While Australia is looking at a baby boom, it also suffers from an aging population like most of the developed countries. With more people crossing to the other side of 45 and increased advancements in medical treatment technologies, the demand for healthcare and medical professionals is on the rise. Expected forecasts of the industry for 2019 stands at 16.3percentt. The same forecasts also suggest a shortfall of more than 100,000 nurses in Australia by the year 2050.</p>
<p>Students who are aspiring doctors or are inclined towards providing healthcare services, Australia offers an excellent job prospect for years to come.</p>
<p>It is, however, important to note here that usually the Australian Medical programs are very expensive and run for about 5 years. You can plan your studies in Australia and start by learning all about <a href="https://studyabroad.shiksha.com/medicine-from-australia-structure-eligibility-exams-required-validity-articlepage-569" target="_blank">Medicine from Australia – Structure, Eligibility, Exams required and Validity</a> of the program.</p>
<p><strong>3. Construction and Architects</strong></p>
<p>This sector, though slated to boom at about 10 percent by 2020, essentially requires more skilled workers. The demand for plumbers, electricians and stonemason are ripe and voluminous. However, what is important to note here is that as the building industry rises, so would the demand for Civil Engineers, Electrical Engineers and also Architects and Interior Designers. If you are inclined towards the trade, then Australia is sure to offer you an excellent opportunity to not only find a job but also seek your own ventures.</p>
<p>The industry is essentially looking for qualified engineers and architects. Engineering students can also look at courses like Construction Planning and Management. Also, the more the projects, the more the requirement for qualified Project Managers – deftly provided by qualified MBA professionals. So both <a href="https://studyabroad.shiksha.com/ms-in-architecture-from-australia-ds11509262" target="_blank">Architecture in Australia</a>, as well as <a href="https://studyabroad.shiksha.com/mba-in-australia-dc11508" target="_blank">MBA Colleges in Australia</a> would continue to be a safe bet!</p>
<p><strong>4. Information and Communication Technology</strong></p>
<p>Digitization is a global phenomenon which has triggered a wide requirement of IT and Telecommunications Professionals. Australia too faces the same requirement, making ICT one of the leading sectors with a steady demand for qualified professionals. Forecasted to grow at a rate of 12 percent, the companies are forever on the lookout for fresh talent to accommodate the fast-paced technological changes.</p>
<p>Students aspiring for engineering degrees in IT and Communications are, hence, sure to find relevant opportunities in Australia. It is worthwhile to mention that Computer Networking Professionals are to have the highest demand with industry expecting to increase by a whopping 20 percent by 2019, just about the time when you would complete your <a href="https://studyabroad.shiksha.com/ms-in-australia-dc11509" target="_blank">MS  from Australia</a>!</p>
<p>To sum up, if you are planning to study in Australia, there are plenty of opportunities open to students across domains!</p>		<!-- Download Guide Widget STARTS-->

